The paper deals with action recognition in video data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of bag-of-visual-words pipeline and visual vocabulary generation also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of subsampling and partitioning, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
